29:14.525 --> 29:15.359
Somebody!

29:15.442 --> 29:17.403
[roar of vehicles]

29:19.488 --> 29:21.699
[siren in the background]

29:48.142 --> 29:49.142
[sighs]

30:17.004 --> 30:19.340
Margo. Hi!

30:20.257 --> 30:21.800
Vera! Ed!

30:21.884 --> 30:23.636
[Vera] Hey, what are you doing here?

30:23.719 --> 30:25.137
I have a book signing.

30:25.220 --> 30:28.098
Oh, you should have told us,
we would have come.

30:28.182 --> 30:30.601
Is it the marriage book or something new?

30:31.060 --> 30:33.479
The marriage book. I'm the expert.

30:33.562 --> 30:35.105
[chuckles]

30:36.482 --> 30:39.693
Listen, I know we haven't been the best...

30:39.777 --> 30:41.737
We did call you about that dinner.

30:41.820 --> 30:44.782
It's just... it's been
really difficult for us

30:44.865 --> 30:48.577
to navigate the whole...

30:48.661 --> 30:51.455
and Stephen was really struggling there
for awhile.

30:52.873 --> 30:55.668
Well, so good that he has you.

30:56.377 --> 30:57.753
Excuse me, I'm running late.

31:01.715 --> 31:02.967
She's lost a lot of weight.

31:03.509 --> 31:05.886
[music playing over radio]

31:24.697 --> 31:26.532
[Mother] Okay, you're okay.

31:27.282 --> 31:28.492
Here we go.

31:28.867 --> 31:31.036
Some bottles? Bottles?

31:33.414 --> 31:35.582
- How much does he weigh?
- She...

31:37.501 --> 31:39.253
- Really?
- Really.

31:39.753 --> 31:40.963
Sorry.

32:02.192 --> 32:05.112
[baby crying]

32:10.451 --> 32:12.453
What? Have you never seen
a baby's ass before?

32:12.536 --> 32:15.122
[baby crying]

32:19.793 --> 32:21.086
Shh! Shh!

32:21.754 --> 32:24.339
[baby shrieks]

32:28.343 --> 32:30.095
Any questions? Yes?

32:30.179 --> 32:33.599
[Woman] You mentioned that marriage
is the cornerstone of patriarchal power.

32:34.099 --> 32:37.728
I didn't, that was the basis
for the feminist argument in the '70s.

32:37.811 --> 32:39.730
Many people have argued the opposite,

32:39.813 --> 32:42.900
but even in a love-based marriage,

32:42.983 --> 32:45.944
each sex is capable of
harnessing the productive

32:46.028 --> 32:48.238
and reproductive skills of the other.

32:48.322 --> 32:50.407
Couldn't it be that people
didn't want to be alone?

32:52.993 --> 32:55.370
Well, that would have made for
a shorter book.

32:55.454 --> 32:56.914
[audience members laugh]

33:10.469 --> 33:11.469
Hey.

33:13.972 --> 33:16.183
Buddy? Hey!

33:19.353 --> 33:21.647
Hey! Oh, my God!

33:23.023 --> 33:25.192
Oh, my God, no!

33:25.275 --> 33:26.276
No!

33:26.360 --> 33:27.444
No!

33:35.494 --> 33:38.747
[crying] Oh, my God!

33:48.465 --> 33:50.676
[sobs]

33:50.759 --> 33:51.885
[doorbell buzzes]

34:03.355 --> 34:04.481
Yes?

34:05.315 --> 34:07.359
[Manuel] <i> Mrs. Mooney,</i>
<i>that girl, she's here.</i>

34:08.860 --> 34:10.195
Send her up!

34:14.741 --> 34:19.538
Oh! I'm sorry.

34:24.751 --> 34:26.587
[knock on door]

34:32.676 --> 34:36.054
I need to find Nico. Please!

34:36.263 --> 34:38.306
Look, I'm his girlfriend, Tallulah.

34:40.684 --> 34:41.726
Whose baby is this?

34:46.231 --> 34:47.274
It's his.

35:02.748 --> 35:03.790
How old is she?

35:03.874 --> 35:05.250
She's one.

35:05.542 --> 35:07.127
[Margo] She's big for one.

35:08.128 --> 35:09.129
She's almost two.

35:10.464 --> 35:11.984
Oh, can you take that out of her hand?

35:12.591 --> 35:13.634
Oh, yeah.

35:17.012 --> 35:18.847
- I got it.
- What's her name?

35:18.931 --> 35:21.892
Margaret. We named her after you.

35:23.477 --> 35:25.896
Never liked the name Margaret.
That's why I go by Margo.

35:25.979 --> 35:27.356
Well, we call her Maggie,

35:27.439 --> 35:30.067
so really, Maggie's her name.

35:30.150 --> 35:32.110
- [Margo] Can you just...
- She's all right.

35:32.986 --> 35:34.363
She's fine, she's like...

35:35.155 --> 35:38.242
a little... I'll put her in gymnastics
when she's older, for sure.

35:39.117 --> 35:41.328
[Tallulah] Oh, my God!
I have something for you.

35:43.914 --> 35:45.415
Nico said you wanted us to use it.

35:49.294 --> 35:51.614
If I wanted you to use it,
I would've given you permission.

35:51.672 --> 35:53.090
This is called stealing.

35:53.924 --> 35:55.300
You could have closed the account.

35:56.885 --> 35:59.346
And how else could I keep track of my son?

35:59.596 --> 36:01.682
I have a record of every
gas station in every city.

36:01.765 --> 36:04.643
You've been all over.
Can you please put that down?

36:06.019 --> 36:07.187
Sorry.

36:08.522 --> 36:10.691
[Margo] I had no idea it was with a baby.

36:12.025 --> 36:13.443
Why didn't he call me?

36:14.361 --> 36:16.280
I don't know. He just...

36:16.363 --> 36:18.198
he said that he wanted to come home.

36:18.282 --> 36:19.449
Oh, now he wants to come home

36:19.533 --> 36:21.743
now that he's knocked up
some homeless girl!

36:21.827 --> 36:25.330
Hey! I am not homeless, okay?

36:25.414 --> 36:28.458
I'm just sleeping in my van,
but a window's broken,

36:28.542 --> 36:30.377
and it's not a safe place for a baby.

36:30.460 --> 36:33.213
Maybe you should have thought of that
before you had one!

36:34.214 --> 36:35.590
Do you want to hold her?

36:36.008 --> 36:38.135
No! I'm not stupid.

36:44.975 --> 36:47.436
One night, one!

36:48.061 --> 36:49.938
This house is full of
very expensive things

36:50.022 --> 36:51.732
and sharp corners, so you hold on to her.

36:51.815 --> 36:56.403
And if you take anything from me,
I will find you.

36:57.237 --> 36:58.989
[voices over police radio]

36:59.406 --> 37:01.384
There's no way that this woman
worked for the hotel.

37:01.408 --> 37:02.659
She was housekeeping.

37:02.743 --> 37:03.952
We have babysitting services.

37:04.036 --> 37:06.621
You would think you people
have protections against this.

37:06.705 --> 37:08.623
[Carolyn] I pay enough for my room.

37:08.707 --> 37:11.126
Was she wearing a hotel uniform?

37:12.210 --> 37:13.045
[in low voice] Yes.

37:13.128 --> 37:14.421
Are you sure?

37:16.006 --> 37:18.342
- Can we get her one to look at?
- Yes, sir.

37:20.844 --> 37:22.596
[radio] <i> Clear, boss, we got nothin'.</i>

37:23.472 --> 37:25.557
Okay, move it out. Level one mobilization.

37:25.640 --> 37:28.310
Tell Central
to start making notifications.

37:28.602 --> 37:29.478
What is that?

37:29.561 --> 37:33.315
Missing Persons, possibly the FBI,
in case she crossed state lines.

37:33.398 --> 37:36.068
[whispers] What if she tries to sell her?

37:36.151 --> 37:39.029
She's white, she's pretty.
People would want her.

37:39.112 --> 37:40.280
I don't think that's likely.

37:41.782 --> 37:43.033
One thing at a time, Ms. Ford.

37:43.116 --> 37:44.409
Or, is it Mrs.?

37:45.952 --> 37:46.953
Yes.

37:47.037 --> 37:48.455
We need to notify your husband.

37:49.915 --> 37:51.958
Oh, he's in London on business.

37:52.042 --> 37:53.668
We'll be asking him some questions,

37:53.752 --> 37:55.879
and we'll be asking you
some questions as well.

37:57.130 --> 37:59.883
- It's not my fault.
- No one thinks it is.

37:59.966 --> 38:02.636
If my baby's hurt,
I don't know what I'll do.

38:05.138 --> 38:06.681
- Elevator and the hallway?
- Yeah.

38:06.765 --> 38:09.226
Put this out to the local news stations
and papers.

38:09.309 --> 38:12.270
News! Haven't I been through enough?

38:13.814 --> 38:15.690
Do you want to find your child?

38:37.504 --> 38:38.672
[whispers] Thanks.

38:40.215 --> 38:41.758
Did you use my toothbrush?

38:43.552 --> 38:45.804
- Maybe.
- Because it was wet.

38:46.304 --> 38:47.304
Sorry.

38:47.347 --> 38:48.765
[Margo] Don't you have one?

38:48.849 --> 38:50.142
Why? Is that gross?

38:50.767 --> 38:52.102
Yes!

38:54.521 --> 38:56.314
Is she all right sleeping there?

38:58.191 --> 38:59.443
Yeah.

39:02.988 --> 39:04.781
Her breathing is so fast.

39:06.032 --> 39:07.576
Is that bad?

39:07.659 --> 39:08.659
No.

39:18.253 --> 39:20.881
Isn't she just the coolest,

39:21.381 --> 39:24.009
weirdest little thing you've ever seen?

39:24.092 --> 39:25.469
Yes.

39:26.428 --> 39:29.139
She's just so little.

39:29.222 --> 39:33.477
She's got those, like,
tiny little toenails,

39:34.519 --> 39:36.146
it just blows my mind.

39:38.315 --> 39:39.542
Then they grow up and hate you,

39:39.566 --> 39:41.693
and it really blows your mind.

39:44.154 --> 39:45.405
Yeah.

39:48.408 --> 39:50.952
Well, good night.

39:51.036 --> 39:52.662
[Tallulah] Good night, Mommy.

39:52.746 --> 39:55.040
Don't use my toothbrush again.

40:06.301 --> 40:08.929
[juicer whirring]

40:24.945 --> 40:26.279
Oh!

40:33.912 --> 40:35.121
What are you doing?

40:35.622 --> 40:36.498
Juicing!

40:36.581 --> 40:38.083
Where did you find that juicer?

40:38.166 --> 40:40.627
Oh, up in the cabinet, still in the box.

40:42.295 --> 40:44.506
Please stop that noise.

40:45.507 --> 40:46.508
Dude.

40:47.092 --> 40:50.262
The guy at the bodega
sold me 16 for a dollar.

40:50.345 --> 40:53.348
They were four for a dollar,
but I talked him down,

40:53.431 --> 40:55.517
or we talked him down, that's right.

40:55.600 --> 40:58.019
I'm gonna make a lemonade
stand on the back of Jim.

40:58.103 --> 40:59.729
- Jim?
- Yeah, it's my van.

40:59.813 --> 41:01.982
Dude, freshly squeezed lemonade.

41:02.065 --> 41:04.192
Are you kidding me? I'm gonna kill.

41:06.486 --> 41:09.030
No, stop that sound. Tallulah, stop it.

41:11.825 --> 41:13.326
[Tallulah] Oh, shit.

41:14.995 --> 41:15.995
[sighs]

41:17.080 --> 41:18.081
Has she eaten?

41:18.957 --> 41:20.584
- Not really.
- All right, I think I...

41:20.667 --> 41:23.169
Oh, God, got some cereal or something.

41:27.966 --> 41:29.134
[Margo] Here you go.

41:29.217 --> 41:31.261
No milk or anything, huh? Just like that?

41:32.095 --> 41:33.722
Are you breast-feeding?

41:33.805 --> 41:35.432
She has a bottle.

41:35.515 --> 41:37.142
Why don't you make her one?

41:37.225 --> 41:39.311
And she needs a change of clothes.

41:39.394 --> 41:41.313
Where are her things?

41:41.396 --> 41:42.689
Stolen.

41:42.772 --> 41:45.609
Some asshole broke into my van,
stole my suitcase.

41:45.692 --> 41:47.902
I got some stuff in the stroller, but...

41:48.695 --> 41:50.614
- Does she have a toy?
- I mean, a couple.

41:50.697 --> 41:54.242
But she doesn't like toys.
She likes things like shoes, pans and

41:54.326 --> 41:56.703
stuff like this.
Do you know what I mean?

41:57.037 --> 41:58.288
Do you have any sugar?

42:03.084 --> 42:07.088
Lemonade! Fresh-squeezed lemonade!

42:08.256 --> 42:11.843
Who wants some lemonade?
You want lemonade?

42:11.926 --> 42:14.679
I know you want lemonade.
Come on, it's organic.

42:14.763 --> 42:16.473
It's organic. You sir, you want some.

42:16.556 --> 42:18.642
You need it. Hydration is important.

42:18.725 --> 42:20.644
Looking at your skin, you need it.

42:20.727 --> 42:22.145
Lemonade, do you want lemonade?

42:22.228 --> 42:24.064
Discount, I'll give you a discount.

42:24.147 --> 42:27.025
You'll enjoy it. Yes. Yes.

42:32.238 --> 42:33.573
[baby whimpers]

42:33.657 --> 42:35.200
You cannot do this here.

42:35.283 --> 42:37.118
Oh, really? Well, what's this?

42:37.202 --> 42:39.287
As if the neighbors don't have enough
to talk about.

42:39.371 --> 42:41.289
Get in the apartment,
this is embarrassing.

42:41.373 --> 42:44.000
No one's even watching, who cares?
Cool down.

42:44.084 --> 42:45.710
The doorman is staring.

42:47.045 --> 42:49.506
The doorman is staring
because he's thirsty.

42:49.589 --> 42:50.507
Lu, no.

42:50.590 --> 42:52.300
It's hot out, dude.

42:54.052 --> 42:57.597
Here, Manny! Enjoy.

42:59.683 --> 43:01.142
Oh, my God.

43:01.226 --> 43:02.226
[horn blares]

43:07.440 --> 43:10.819
Hold on, it's coming up.
I've got the little girl exiting.

43:15.115 --> 43:17.367
- There you go.
- Stop, stop.

43:20.620 --> 43:24.833
Turn around, turn around.

43:26.418 --> 43:27.961
Thank you.

43:29.629 --> 43:31.464
That's her, that's her.

43:32.257 --> 43:34.134
Oh, damn it.

43:34.217 --> 43:36.386
- [Tallulah] Can I do anything?
- No.

43:36.469 --> 43:40.348
I'm fine, just...

43:40.432 --> 43:42.225
stop watching me.

43:42.392 --> 43:44.745
[Tallulah] Do you always get
this stressed out when you cook?

43:44.769 --> 43:47.230
Well, I don't usually have an audience.

43:49.190 --> 43:51.609
Do you have a turtle or frog or something?

43:51.693 --> 43:54.487
- No.
- Just a tank?

43:54.571 --> 43:56.322
It died, years ago.

43:56.406 --> 43:57.907
I don't know why I still keep it.

43:57.991 --> 43:59.117
Oh! Oh!

43:59.200 --> 44:00.535
Here, let me help.

44:05.123 --> 44:06.666
Were you raised by wolves?

44:06.750 --> 44:08.293
I wish.

44:08.918 --> 44:11.921
Okay, stop. Get out of the kitchen.

44:12.005 --> 44:14.090
Take her, and wash your hands
while you're at it.

44:14.674 --> 44:17.969
[mouth full] Okay. Come on, munchkin.

44:31.149 --> 44:32.275
Chicken's dry.

44:32.776 --> 44:35.612
At least it's not dirty like the broccoli.

44:39.407 --> 44:41.826
You might want to cut that up for her.

44:43.369 --> 44:44.621
Hmm.

44:44.704 --> 44:46.456
Those books have your name on them.

44:46.539 --> 44:47.749
I wrote them.

44:47.832 --> 44:48.832
What are they about?

44:49.918 --> 44:52.837
The family unit,
from a historical perspective.

44:52.921 --> 44:56.216
My last book was about cultural shifts
in the perception of marriage.

44:56.299 --> 44:57.383
It's fucked up.

44:58.510 --> 45:00.094
Yes, in a nutshell.

45:02.055 --> 45:03.723
Is that how you afford all this?

45:05.099 --> 45:05.934
All this?

45:06.017 --> 45:09.062
Well, the furniture
and the fancy paintings and...

45:09.562 --> 45:12.440
Hmm. Most of it's my husband's.

45:12.899 --> 45:14.859
The fancy paintings are his.

45:14.943 --> 45:16.486
Why didn't you change it?

45:16.945 --> 45:18.613
I can't. This is faculty housing.

45:18.696 --> 45:20.198
No one can know he's not here.

45:20.281 --> 45:22.200
Come on. Are they really checking?

45:25.787 --> 45:28.498
It would drive me crazy,
living with someone else's stuff.

45:28.581 --> 45:31.125
I mean, it's one thing
if it's your own shitty art.

45:32.502 --> 45:33.795
You're very rude.

45:35.255 --> 45:36.589
[sighs] I'll stop talking.

45:46.140 --> 45:47.684
I hate the paintings.

45:48.893 --> 45:49.894
Happy?

45:52.564 --> 45:55.024
[distant siren]

47:34.624 --> 47:37.251
[buzzer]

47:37.335 --> 47:40.213
[engine revs]

47:44.217 --> 47:45.718
Fuck!

47:53.267 --> 47:56.145
[knocking]

48:09.033 --> 48:10.034
[Margo] Were you leaving?

48:10.118 --> 48:12.870
I'm not used to sleeping in a bed.
I'm comfortable in the van.

48:12.954 --> 48:15.581
It's not safe to leave a baby alone.
Didn't anyone tell you?

48:15.665 --> 48:18.084
I'm figuring out this whole "mommy" thing
on my own.

48:18.167 --> 48:20.044
- You have no idea what you're doing.
- I know.

48:20.128 --> 48:22.088
I cannot believe this kid
has made it this far.

48:22.171 --> 48:24.173
I have half a mind to call Child Services.

48:24.257 --> 48:25.091
Well, fuck!

48:25.174 --> 48:26.926
I've never done this before, okay?

48:27.009 --> 48:28.886
You ask about these things, Tallulah.

48:28.970 --> 48:30.930
No one knows how to do it, but you ask.

48:31.013 --> 48:33.057
Well, I've never had anyone to ask.

48:36.310 --> 48:37.437
[children laughing]

48:42.150 --> 48:43.484
[whistling]

48:44.360 --> 48:47.321
[whistling]

48:52.243 --> 48:55.121
Well, don't eat the grass.
Don't eat the grass.

48:56.664 --> 48:59.208
I guess I shouldn't knock it
before I try it.

49:02.295 --> 49:03.546
It's not good.

49:05.590 --> 49:06.924
Don't do it.

49:08.217 --> 49:09.469
What's your plan, Lu?

49:11.971 --> 49:13.723
Lie in the grass?

49:13.806 --> 49:15.808
I mean, with your life.

49:18.603 --> 49:19.645
Did you have a plan?

49:19.729 --> 49:21.230
Yes, of course I did.

49:21.314 --> 49:22.899
And what was that?

49:23.649 --> 49:26.736
Well, I suppose it changed.

49:26.819 --> 49:30.656
I was finishing my thesis
when I got pregnant.

49:31.073 --> 49:34.660
All of our friends were these
hyper-academic, ambitious people

49:34.744 --> 49:37.747
and Stephen was right there
at the center of it all.

49:38.414 --> 49:40.291
I suppose it wasn't cool to admit it,

49:40.374 --> 49:43.753
because it was painfully conventional,

49:43.836 --> 49:49.050
but I really just wanted to be married,

49:51.552 --> 49:53.221
and to have a family.

49:53.304 --> 49:54.806
My plan was to be a mom.

49:55.306 --> 49:56.516
How did that work out?

49:57.850 --> 49:59.852
I guess it didn't. They both left me.

50:02.814 --> 50:04.732
[Tallulah] You're naive,
that's your problem.

50:04.816 --> 50:06.818
[Margo] Don't say that. I hate that word.

50:07.985 --> 50:10.363
Your plan depended on other people.

50:10.446 --> 50:13.991
People suck, and they'll
disappoint you every time.

50:14.075 --> 50:15.618
That is no way to live.

50:16.244 --> 50:18.704
Look, I'm not saying
that we should go around,

50:18.788 --> 50:22.291
dicking each other over
all the time, but...

50:22.875 --> 50:24.252
like, look...

50:25.920 --> 50:27.213
When I was six,

50:27.296 --> 50:31.425
my mom took me
to this weird apartment building,

50:31.509 --> 50:35.054
and she sat me up on the stoop,
and told me to wait.

50:35.555 --> 50:38.599
And she was just gonna go run
some errands,

50:38.683 --> 50:40.059
and come back.

50:40.810 --> 50:43.271
And, um...

50:43.354 --> 50:47.191
I sat there for hours,
and it got really cold,

50:47.275 --> 50:50.236
and then, this old Buick pulls up

50:50.319 --> 50:53.823
and this tall skinny guy gets out.

50:53.906 --> 50:56.367
A guy I'd never even seen before,

50:57.410 --> 51:01.330
and he was like, "Hey, I'm your dad

51:01.414 --> 51:03.916
and you're gonna come home with me."

51:07.628 --> 51:09.672
Um... and then I never... I...

51:11.465 --> 51:13.092
I never saw her again.

51:15.928 --> 51:18.514
But I wouldn't have cared
if I hadn't needed her.

51:18.598 --> 51:19.932
So...

51:21.976 --> 51:24.395
I just think it's better to not be needed.

51:26.397 --> 51:28.024
She needs you.

51:28.107 --> 51:29.775
She doesn't know any better!

51:30.067 --> 51:33.195
You cannot keep living
in your van, it's dangerous.

51:33.279 --> 51:35.031
- You live alone.
- It's not the same!

51:35.114 --> 51:37.867
You're out on the street,
you could be robbed or attacked!

51:37.950 --> 51:39.702
You could slip in the shower,

51:39.785 --> 51:41.871
choke on an egg roll or something.

51:42.371 --> 51:43.372
Who would find you?

51:43.456 --> 51:45.207
No one. For days!

51:46.375 --> 51:48.255
My cleaning lady
would have a horrible surprise.

51:48.294 --> 51:50.004
Yes! That poor woman!

51:50.087 --> 51:51.631
- Yeah.
- Don't do that to someone.

51:55.426 --> 51:58.012
Thank God there's gravity, right?

51:58.095 --> 51:59.889
What do you mean?

51:59.972 --> 52:02.475
Hmm, like just sticking us
here on the ground.

52:04.143 --> 52:06.938
Like some magnet at the center
of the earth and the lava,

52:07.021 --> 52:08.481
just keeping us stuck.

52:08.564 --> 52:09.982
It's not a magnet.

52:11.692 --> 52:14.028
What if it stopped, you know?

52:14.111 --> 52:15.112
Or what if it stopped

52:15.196 --> 52:18.866
just right in the spot where I was?

52:19.867 --> 52:21.410
